<br>
As a 216 skilled Potter, I am capable of creating Faithstones for Clerics or Spiritstones for Shaman (all but Vah Shir). These are Right Click items usable in a general inventory slot that will port you (and only you) to your Home Temple. It takes 30 seconds to cast this effect. Faithstones for Clerics weigh 0.1 each and Spiritstones for Shaman weigh 20.0 each.  Each Stone has an Infinite number of Charges on it.  You will NEVER run out of Ports.<br>
<br>
There are SO many combinations of Clerics and Shaman out there that it is IMPOSSIBLE for me to keep all of them in stock. Basically what I'm hoping to do, long term, here is to keep in stock Faithstones of Nature (High Elven Clerics), Faithstones of Hate (Dark Elven Clerics), Faithstones of Courage (ALL Human Clerics regardless of who they worship, though this could EASILY be chagned soon to only allow those worshiping Mithanial or Erollisi Marr), and Faithstones of the Underfoot (Dwarven Clerics, just don't know the name offhand). Why these 4? Simple, those 4 combos make up 80% of the Cleric population.<br>
<br>
Now, the way I am going to sell these will work like this. If (and this is a big IF at the present), I have them in stock, I sell Stones for 10k. <br>
<br>
Now the OTHER way to get these from me is this. Talk to me in game. Then bring me the components. Specifically, bring me Distilled Mana and/or Iron Oxides. Each Stone also requires an &quot;Essence&quot; to create. If you can bring me those Essences, that's great and I'll work on a better price for you but the Essences are NOT the bottleneck in creating these (contrary to popular belief). The bottlenecks are the Distilled Mana and the Iron Oxides. As a Cleric myself, I have no good way of getting either of these. You will NOT pay me for any failures. The cost of the Materials that you paid was already enough. However, you WILL pay for the first success. Since you're bringing me the components, it will be MUCH less than if I'm selling one on the market. Probably in the neighborhood of 1 to 3k depending on the exact situation. After the first success, we can determine then what we want to do with any left over materials.<br>
<br>
Distilled Mana: Created by a Level 39+ Enchanter and requires a Poison Vial and 2 Sapphires (105pp each at best prices).<br>
<br>
Iron Oxides: Ground Spawns in Steamfont and RARE drops from Elementals. The ground spawns have 6 spots that they spawn and those spawns are on 12 hour timers.  The good news is that I don't need many of these.  Pottery is a 2 stage process with 99% of my failures in the first stage.  Iron Oxides are used in the 2nd stage which I nearly always succeed.<br>
<br>
Now there is a couple things to keep in mind:<br>
1: I may or may not have the Essence in stock at the time. If I don't, you are either going to have to get it for me or I will need to get it myself.<br>
<br>
2: It is VERY helpful if you bring components for, roughly, 10 attempts. At 213 skill I believe I am the 2nd highest Potter on the server. Even with this skill I still fail a LOT. It is still possible for me to fail 10 attempts in a row but that is also not likely. Keep in mind though that this is a risk you take. When I combine, we WILL group up so you can see my successes/failures. I won't hide it from you.<br>
<br>
3: I'm a member of Affliction. A PROUD member of Affliction. We are a raiding guild. We don't raid everyday but we raid a LOT. If you send me a tell while I'm on a raid, don't be suprised if I reply with &quot;Sorry, raiding now. Can't talk.&quot; or ignore you completely. I have NOTHING against you. High Level Raids are VERY stressful for a Cleric and I might not be able to take the time to talk. Also, the same goes for if I tell you &quot;Hey, I'm a bit busy right now, catch me some other time.&quot;<br>
<br>
For more information on all of this, go visit www.eqtraders.com. There is a wealth of info on these things. If you have any questions on Pottery or making these yourselves, read the site or feel free to talk to me in game. Honestly I don't mind. In fact if someone wants to totally put me out of business by getting their Pottery up and mass producing this stuff, that's fine. I originally got into to this to make MY Stone and Stones for Guildmates.  <p>Baroness <A Href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6975" Style="text-decoration: none">Quistil Angelwatch</a><br>High Priest in the service to the Great Mother Tunare <br>
